task.summary: Default task
Add a folder, so that project works better when first downloaded
Added a staff you need to make magic
Make begginningRoom one space longer for asthetics
Staff gives Tip when picked up
Clean up Spark class

Added a new. less obnoxious text box!
It doesn't cover the whole screen and nicely chains together to create dialog! It even includes the speaker's name!
It's amazing!
CompactTextBox retry
Added a half-made inventory
Expanded on Spells and Enemies
Clean up the basement and add a pot of petunias in it to kill.
Add dropped items, made petunia pot drop a Spark spell, delete redundant Spark class (use Spell instead)
fixed player freeze on opening new menus (from earlier deletion of player.update()), worked a bit on inventory
Dropping items is slightly better. Still keeps trying to update it, though.
Work on inventory. Now has correct (but unused) selector and puts thing in spots nicely.
Fixed bug #4, it was cuz the room variable wasn't being set and then things failed silently.
Change all the inventory stuff to be in Inventory.java, improved on spell setting and storage.
Redo how getSelectedItem in inventory is called, add javadocs
Rename Enemy to Mortal, made Player a Mortal
Fix spellcasting (Inventory.getSelectedName stuff was getting description instead, getSelectedDescription getting name)
Added a dangerous Spike to tutorial basement that drops a Flame spell, and modernized that class. You can also now be killed.
Add more spells! Wanderer and various healing ones.
Made tutorial dialoge for spike occur before getting hit by spells.
Clean up Room.java

Added Window Config class
Presets don't work yet. Everything else does. Need to do some tweaks.
Make the boat level! It's fun!
Made window sizer automatic and tell you creepy stuff
Some cleanup of Room.java (needs more on naming of hitmesh methods)
You are now given a personalized message from your killer upon your death.
Spike suicides upon hopeless situations (like moved out of world with dock)
Add a mountain trail setting, where you can fall off the edge.
Made mtns and player hurt mechanism slightly less annoying
New inventory is half-built. I don't see how we'll get as many items in here, though.
FWIW, Trolls and stuff on the mountain trail chase you.
Roughly double FPS. Profiling told me that Window.build() was taking 150ms; now takes 40-70ms.
repackaging - make folder for Zone 1, etc

Back from vacation. Tried making a new Menu object so we could get a clean starrt at building a new inventory screen.
Having some trouble, though.
Make red-text-when-Player-Hurt better, and generally quiet sout. I did stuff.

The humble beginnings of a truly user-friendly menu. Push Q to experience the New Menu Betaâ„¢
The A button is used to confirm options, rather than ENTER.

I'm on vacation, but there is also internet here too! Testing GitHub on my laptop.
I also added a new window in the Spells equipment page. It now shows what you have currently equipped. Even though you can already figure it out beforehand....

THE INTRO IS COMPLETE!
